## What is Categorical Data Analysis?

-   In BSTA 512/612 (linear regression), we focused on [continuous responses/outcomes]{style="color:#34AC8B; font-weight: bold;"}

    -   We included [categorical variables only as covariates]{style="color:#34AC8B; font-weight: bold;"} (aka predictors, independent variables, explanatory variables)

    -   Examples from 512/612: life expectancy (in years), IAT score (ranging from -2 to 2)

Â  Â 

-   Categorical data analysis focuses on the statistical methods for [categorical responses/outcomes]{style="color:#213c96; font-weight: bold;"}

    -   Explanatory (or â€˜independentâ€™) variable can be of any type (continuous or categorical)

